1. WHAT IS A LAMBDA?

A lambda is an anonymous function (compiler-generated functor) that can capture variables from its surrounding scope.

Syntax:

[capture](parameters) specifiers -> return_type
{
    // body
};

Example:

auto add = [](int a, int b)
{
    return a + b;
};

